1. add springdoc-openapi-starter-webmvc-ui dependency to the department-service (from maven repository)
2. then run config server and service registry then run the department-service
3. go to browser type: localhost:8080/swagger-ui/index.html
4. in order to get the rest-apis in a json format open new window type: localhost:8080/v3/api-docs

II. Defining general API information(using annotations)
1. annotate main entry point of the class with @OpenAPIDefination(
info = @Info(
    title ="Department Service Rest Api",
    Description ="Department service Rest Api's Documentation"
    Version ="v1.0",
    contact = @Contact(
    name ="seema"
    email="seema@gmail.com"
    url ="https:www.javaguides.com"),
    license = "Apache 2.0",
    url ="https:www.javaguides.com"
),
externalDocs=@ExternalDocumentation(
    description ="Department service Doc",
    url ="https:www.javaguides.com"
)
)
